  "body": "In my private net when `geth` reads my blockchain at startup it shows that Byzantium is not enabled:\r\n`INFO [10-26|21:50:50] Initialised chain configuration          config=\"{ChainID: 555 Homestead: <nil> DAO: <nil> DAOSupport: false EIP150: <nil> EIP155: <nil> EIP158: <nil> Byzantium: <nil> Engine: unknown}\"`\r\n\r\nhowever I did set it in the config file to 0:\r\n\r\n```\r\n    MainnetChainConfig = &ChainConfig{\r\n        ChainId:        big.NewInt(555),\r\n        HomesteadBlock: big.NewInt(math.MaxInt64),\r\n        DAOForkBlock:   big.NewInt(math.MaxInt64),\r\n        DAOForkSupport: false,\r\n        EIP150Block:    big.NewInt(0),\r\n        EIP150Hash:     common.HexToHash(\"0x2086799aeebeae135c246c65021c82b4e15a2c451340993aacfd2751886514f0\"),\r\n        EIP155Block:    big.NewInt(0),\r\n        EIP158Block:    big.NewInt(0),\r\n        ByzantiumBlock: big.NewInt(0),\r\n\r\n        Ethash: new(EthashConfig),\r\n    }\r\n\r\n```\r\nthe isByzantium() function is returning `nil` because c.ByzantiumBlock is nill, and it is nil because my blockchain genesis block doesn't have it. \r\n```\r\nfunc (c *ChainConfig) IsByzantium(num *big.Int) bool {\r\n    return isForked(c.ByzantiumBlock, num)\r\n}\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nNow, my question is, can I hard code this function and return isByzantium() to always `true` ?\r\nOr should I do some migration process to convert existing blockchain to Byzantium? \r\nI can stop and restart my private net, but I can't recalculate the blockchain, so what are my options to convert it to Byzantium?\r\n\r\n",
